<span id="freeTextContainer310319955228910362">Gary Bregar has a passion for all things creative.<br/><br/>He enjoys traveling, and prefers to see the world through the eyes of local residents whenever possible. During his travels one might have caught a glimpse of him climbing the pyramids of Chichén Itzá, Mexico, touring the wine country of Tarija, Bolivia, or exploring the glaciers of Iceland. He also enjoys weekends of camping, hiking, or skiing.<br/><br/>Gar</span>
  <span id="freeText310319955228910362" style="display:none">Gary Bregar has a passion for all things creative.<br /><br />He enjoys traveling, and prefers to see the world through the eyes of local residents whenever possible. During his travels one might have caught a glimpse of him climbing the pyramids of Chichén Itzá, Mexico, touring the wine country of Tarija, Bolivia, or exploring the glaciers of Iceland. He also enjoys weekends of camping, hiking, or skiing.<br /><br />Gary believes in strong community involvement, and has volunteered as both organizer and public speaker for several organizations.<br /><br />In addition to being an avid reader, he has an affinity for art, film, comics, and all things creative. It should also be mentioned that he is proud to have a near-juvenile interest in such things as The Simpsons, Pink Floyd, and Batman.<br /><br />Originally born and raised in Pueblo, Colorado, Gary currently resides in Idaho Springs, Colorado. <br /> <br /></span>
